The Nigerian National Petroleum Corporation (NNPC) on Thursday in Abuja, reported an oil pipeline fire outbreak, along Atlas Cove-Mosimi Pipeline, otherwise, called  System 2B  pipeline in Baruwa Swamp area of Lagos. According to the corporation, preliminary reports of the incident indicated that the pipeline might have been torched by act of vandalism by suspected oil thieves, who had hacked into the line to intercept flow of petrol. In conjunction with the Lagos State Fire Service, NNPC had deployed various categories of personnel to the scene to bring the fire under control. NNPC assured the general public that the pipeline will be put back into operation shortly, while the breach has no impact on petroleum products supply in the area. It also confirmed that it had 116 million litres of PMS in Mosimi Depot, 7.5 million litres in Satellite Depot and 35 million litres in Ibadan depots, all within System 2B network. Like!! Great article post.Really thank you! Really Cool.